Since $\cos x = 0,$ $x$ is of the form $x = \frac{\pi}{2} + k \pi,$ where $k$ is an integer.  Then $\cos (x + z) = \cos \left( \frac{\pi}{2} + k \pi + z \right) = -\sin z.$  Hence, $-\sin z = \frac{1}{2},$ so $\sin z = -\frac{1}{2}.$

